<span class="name"><a name="29669"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>Are we content with our current Alternate Abilities?</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Tirshatha</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=29669&amp;sid=29511c9804572408bf0315af1e252e21#29669"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Wed Jan 29, 2003 3:36 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">The short answwer for me is HELL NO!! It took Verant what? About 9 months or so to finally roll out some Beastlord AA’a  and how did they turn out? Spectacularly mundane.  
<br />

<br />
Paragon of Spirit this started out lame and turned halfway decent when they upgraded it but it could still use a boost in the amount of mana it gives. For some of the 65 crowd 450 mana is barely half a bubble, not very impressive. 
<br />

<br />
Frenzy of Spirit 250 ATK and 99% haste, WHOA!!! That’s ubber right? No not really, 250 atk is admittedly nice but not for only 45 seconds and 99% haste almost totally useless. Your average level 60 to 65 Beastlord is gonna have a nice haste item (40%) and can caste celerity or alacrity (40%-50%) so that puts him/her right at the haste cap of 85% if I’m not mistaken. So that means the extra 99% haste means JACK SQUAT!! Oh yeah, and you gotta wait 12 minutes between uses. The base reuse time really needs to be lowered and/or the duration lengthened and the 99% must break the haste cap like bard songs do or it’s essentially useless and does little more than give the illusion that this is a decent AA. 
<br />

<br />
Hobble of Spirit now here’s a real winner. I think I’d waste AA points in upping my INT and CHA before I’d put them into this AA. I don’t have it, but from what I’ve read from those that do it gives the pet a very weak snare ability such that a fleeing mob is only rendered immobile when it reaches 5% health. Also you can’t have a normal pet proc on top of it. This AA needs to be changed so that the snare will stop a fleeing mob at 20% and there either needs to be a 150 point DD along with it or it needs to stack with our normal pet procs.
<br />

<br />
WHOA!!! WHOA!!! WHOA!!! Tirshatha have you gone mad?? We can’t ask for those changes, the big mean men at SoE will come out with their nerf bats and beat us senseless! I simply don’t understand this line of thinking. These are Class AA abilities, these are the things that are supposed to take us to the next level. These are supposed to be on par with Dire charm, manaburn and Archery Mastery + Endless Quiver. 
<br />
Now let’s talk about the unique Planes of Power Beastlord Alternate Abilities…oh that’s right WE DIDN’T GET ANY!! That’s right boys and girls we didn’t get any AA’s that we can call our own, they’re all rehashed AA’s from other classes (yes even double attack, bards get it too) I didn’t want to turn this into a rant but I seemed to fail at that. I wanted this to be a call to arms. Let Sony know that we are not happy with the Beastlord AA situation and if they truly value our patronage that they need to do something about it before they move onto another gimmick filled expansion. 
<br />

<br />
I think the thing that gets me most is people are afraid to demand things that seem reasonable. Earlier I saw a suggestion that we get an AA ability to raise our piercing and 1Hblunt above the 225 cap. WTH?! I don’t want another useless AA to raise a skill that in all honesty should be capped the same as our HTH skill to begin with. There seems to be this group of people with the mindset that we can’t be given something nice without giving up something. Come on people, these AA’s are supposed to make our power go up not shift it around from side to side. Just be bold don’t fear the nerf bat.
<br />

<br />
Some good suggestions that I’ve seen:
<br />

<br />
Animal form:  (no not merge with warder) changing form to that of some kind of beast and gaining certain ability boosts like high regen, increased atk, mana regen, ect… Much like the shaman rabid bear or rangers wolf form.
<br />

<br />
Tracking: some form of tracking akin to bard and druid tracking. It seems to suite our class fine
<br />
note. Schezar please come up with something a little better than eye lasers and Death Touch rings, come on man, tracking is not nearly as powerful as you make it out to be.
<br />

<br />
Support debuffer: while not really an AA I kinda like the idea. A complete line of spells that compliment other spells. IE a 10% slow that stacked with every other slow in the game, a tash like spell that added 5 or 10 more MR reduction and stacked with tash, mini malo, mini cripple, ect…ect…Essentially what out spiritual purity line of spells do now, no way are they as good as C3 or C4 but since it stacks it makes mana regen that much more effective.
<br />

<br />
There are others but it’s late and I can’t think of them.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
