<span class="postbody">I think the main reason mosts people havent been bitching is that we are still dazzled by the dps numbers after we invest heavily into our dps aa's post 60. Well guess what once the other melee classes decide to invest in these aa's we will once again be left in the dust. As far as the aa's you mentioned earlier those blow just as much as the aa to raise our combat caps to 250.. If verant wants to give me AA's it will have to be passive aa's that improve our dmg output.. An AA is missing to improve our pets dmg output, and hell with the latest addition to crap charm spells to every pet class but the beastlord our pet needs some buffing considering magicians, necros, enchanters and druids all can charm pets with a dps of at least 300 with little or no penalty vs. reward. I say we should get a passive aa for our pets that will add around 15dps and 700hp to our per per level and finally top off as our pet cranking out 100 dps with around 6700hp. Also another AA that would be nice would be to give us a self only ferocity or savagery aa that we can keep up at all times.
<br />

<br />
Now spells that I would like to see would be self torpor and a good line of self only buffs maybe a self only haste spell thats on par with enchanters haste or self only ac and attack buff..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
