<span class="name"><a name="32026"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#10:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>Partial agreements</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Uusk</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=32026&amp;sid=29511c9804572408bf0315af1e252e21#32026"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Wed Feb 05, 2003 1:13 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">The one thing I whole heartedly agree with is that we should absolutely get MGB.  No question.  I believe I spend more time at raids buffing people than ANY other class, between individual shrinking, group purity and group vigor (I usually modulate and paragon just to buff everyone and thats with me having C5 and SD).
<br />

<br />
Let me repeat that, I want MGB bad !
<br />

<br />
Paragon : I am on the side of the camp that thinks this is pretty damn good.  Not the level of DC, SoTW, MB or other really nice class AA's...but if we got MGB, I think it would be.  If we get MGB, leave this the way it is.  If we don't, it could use some more kick if this is going to be our 'special' AA.
<br />

<br />
DPS : I think part of the reason there is so much disagreement within the BST ranks about this is people are really coming at this from different points of view.  Some people are looking at their level 40 BST, some are looking at their 65 BST.  Some are comparing us to pure melee classes, some are comparing us to hybrids and casters.  Some are using xp mobs and some are using raid mobs.  Some are using average equipped BST, some are using elemental plane 2HBs.
<br />

<br />
I think our comparative DPS is VERY dependent on all of those factors and any concerns of a specific situation (say, high level raid mobs where everyone has good gear) are ultimately going to get lost because the person who isn't in that situation (say, some BST grinding in Seb) will contradict that person, saying their DPS is fine (which it is).  Those are just examples, the point is ultimately that we should probably try to break down the situations into general categories.
<br />

<br />
One note to people who parse : Remember you are parsing your spell damage and your procs but you aren't parsing everyone elses.  If you are comparing yourself to a pure melee, you shouldn't be.  A mage that blows their mana is going to have a HUGE DPS (that you won't see) and still has a pretty sweet sustainable DPS as well, a melee that doesn't use mana at all will have more consistent damage but not have to hassle with buffing/spell casting time/mana.  We are definitely a hybrid in this respect, we use a combination of melee and mana, maybe more so than any other class, to do our damage.  Now I admit that I haven't seen the uber H2H's so maybe once you have 150AA and that nice 20/19 weapon, you don't chain nuke anymore, I have no idea <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Hobble, root, snare : I don't think we need to have our role expanded into crowd control but it would be sweet for soloing/duoing (assuming hobble was useful in the first place).  Only thing is, in the low to mid level, we are already great soloers.  At the higher levels, I have done some agro kiting...snare would have made it safer but ultimately, with me not in melee, pet just kills mobs way too slow anyway.  I don't think we would be overpowered if we got it but I don't think we really need it either so, to me, its a big red herring and I would rather focus on other issues.
<br />

<br />
Tracking, Pet merging, Animal Form, other 'candy' :
<br />
Would be nice, I wouldn't mind having new toys to play with every once in a while.  Like I said, most of our AA's are pretty boring but, then again, my BST is a lot of fun so I don't feel like I was slighted in that department <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
DPS increasing AA's for pets :
<br />
At first, I thought this would be real nice but as I see better and better gear, I tend to think that I don't want my DPS tied to my pet.  The more DPS is tied to my pet, the less use I get out of gear.  Given that BST don't get access to a lot of good caster gear/FT items/focus items like the other, pure caster, pet classes, we have to be more dependent on our weapons to do damage.  It's already clear that we get less use out of gear, just by being a hybrid (H2H/armor goes to monks, FT goes to pure casters), but we don't get the advantage of really nice, class specific weapons/armor like pally's and SK's.  While patterns/kael type turn in armors are technically class specific, they aren't really, not when it is time to decide who can make good use out of it.
<br />

<br />
One caveat...I wouldn't mind an AA that allowed my pet to borrow, somehow, my melee DPS.  In the same way that pets share our resistances, I could see a Weapon Symbiosis that lets them share the benefit of  our gear (or at least our weapons).  This would serve to not overpower warders early on and yet let them evolve as does our toon.
<br />

<br />
- Uusk TwoShard
<br />
Iksar Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
