<span class="postbody">Hear me out even though I am a mid level Beastlord with No AA.
<br />

<br />
Verant seems to have this problem that can be summed up by this statement : "What is a beastlord"?
<br />

<br />
You see they are not sure what to give us for AA because they are not sure what we are supposed to be.  In my opinion the beastlord should receive AA and PoP AA based around this rule set :
<br />

<br />
Beastlords are Feral warriors who train with beasts and harness the spirits of beasts in order to enhance themselves, their associates and above all else their warders.  We should be to animals / beasts what a necro is to Undead - Masters of them.
<br />

<br />
One AA idea that I think makes a lot of sense and I have seen emntioned is the ability to transform into a Beast and gain certain abilities and stat modifiers based on the form.  Well since a lot fo people DO NOT want to transform into their pet.  How about this idea:
<br />

<br />
Each Beastlord Race turns into a Hybrid form of their Pet :
<br />

<br />
Barbarians - Werewolves - or some other Bipedel Wolf form special ability Massive Regeneration of health with a slightly reduced mana regen maybe soemthing like +20hp per tick stacks with Spiritual line but -5 mana per tick stacks with KEI and spiritual line
<br />

<br />
Iksar - well that one is tough since they are already technically a bipedal reptilian hehe,  heck maybe they can look more like sarnaks. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />
Special ability massive increase in AC but reduced health +100AC / - 500HP
<br />

<br />
Ogre - they can transform into the Tundra Kodiaks at the bear caves in GD - those look cool. Special abilityMassive increase to health but reduced mana +1500 health / - 500 mana
<br />

<br />
Trolls - they can transform into Iksar =P J/k How about they transform into Cazic Thule like Lizard men. special ability Natural speed - +25% haste and constant movement rate = to Just under the fastest bard movement song but reduced mana and hit points -300 mana - 600 hp
<br />

<br />

<br />
Kitty Kats - well as with Iksar they are already humanoid forms or their pet so that again is a tough question. Lets call the form Greater Cat beast for now - kitty kats feel free to suggest a form to suit your race.  The special abilities could be Increased defensive skills +50% chance to succesfully have a defensive skill occur, while incuring a +15% chance to fizzle on spells.
<br />

<br />
Of course each race would have inherent stat increases as well.
<br />

<br />
Some other ideas that are far less thought through :
<br />

<br />
New Spell / trade skill - Spirit fetish :
<br />

<br />
this tradeskill would allow us to create Fetishes that require Spirit gems to be combined with them in order to create a Fetish that could go into the Charm Slot of the new interface.  What these fetishes do is basically give a constant effect buff to ouselves, our groupmates, and all pets as well.  Basically once you activate the fetish it casts a group and group pet spell on all group members and pets and lasts for as long as the group is intact - THIS INCLUDES PETS - so if a member of the group zones, dies or pet dies or is unsummoned then the Fetish is used up and the fetish effect is lost.
<br />

<br />
Come to think of it - I am going to do some research and spend more time thinking this through and post it seperately and maybe we can get a petition going once we have had a chance to read and discuss.
<br />

<br />
Basically a Fetish is like a Potion that effects an entire group including pets but the effects expire for ALL invilved once a party member leaves the group or is killed.  Empty Spirit gems are combined with High quality pelts and meat from animals to harness the spirit of that animal - so a High quality Bear pelt + Bear meat or steaks + Spirit Gem would create a Bear Spirit Gem.  This gem would be combined with a generric Fetish to create a "Fetish of the Bear Spirit" this fetish would have one charge for every Bear Spirit Gem combined with the generic fetish - MAX 5.  This fetish would be Beastlord usable Only and would be equipable in the Charm Slot.  When a charge is used it casts :
<br />
Bear Spirit on the group and the groups pets which could be something like this :
<br />

<br />
+25 STR +50 STA +25 ATK +900HP +45AC - this buff would last until the group was disbanded or a member died / was unsummoned.
<br />

<br />
I know this seems incrediblly overpowered but given the fact that Each fetish would require Much more time and effort then the average Shaman potion and the duration is such a HUGE variable - anywhere from 5 seconds to feesiblly FOREVER as long as No pet, group member dies or leaves group / zone.
<br />

<br />
I had some other ideas for AA but now I beleive I will take my time and write up a proposel for the Create Fetish Class Tradeskill which would be available at level 60 AA.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
